tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a comprehensive visual overhaul,
  introducing a calming sleep-themed color palette, enhancing layout and
  components, and refining section styling to create a more professional and
  engaging user experience.
overview: The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app's
  aesthetics from a generic look to a more beautiful and professional design. I
  began by thoroughly reviewing the existing CSS and component styling,
  identifying a generic color palette, plain backgrounds, and basic form
  elements. The approach involved developing a new, calming sleep-themed color
  palette with deep indigos, purples, and teal accents, which was applied
  globally. Key components like the main questionnaire form, intro section,
  progress bar, checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were redesigned with
  softer shadows, subtle gradients, and improved visual feedback. Section
  groupings were refined from simple gray boxes to more inviting card-like
  structures. The report section also received a significant visual upgrade with
  consistent themed headers and improved content presentation. After
  implementing these changes, I verified the successful compilation and visually
  inspected the app in the browser to ensure the aesthetic goals were met,
  resulting in a more polished and engaging user experience.
